revisions.description: Added port statistics and iSD session statistics.

asfStatistics.name: asfStatistics
asfStatistics.description: Objects under this branch provide statistics.

asfNotifications.name: asfNotifications
asfNotifications.description: This group lists various notifications sent by the ASF system when it encounters defined exceptional conditions.

asfEvents.name: asfEvents
asfEvents.description: This group lists events generated by iSDs in the cluster.

asfAlarms.name: asfAlarms
asfAlarms.description: This group lists alarms generates by iSDs in the cluster. An alarm is a special form of event which represents a fault in the system that needs to be reported.

asfNotificationObjs.name: asfNotificationObjs
asfNotificationObjs.description: This branch consists of objects used to model traps sent to the management station.

deviceIpAddress.name: deviceIpAddress
deviceIpAddress.description: The IP address of the iSD/accelerator emitting the notification.

deviceTimeStamp.name: deviceTimeStamp
deviceTimeStamp.description: The value of the sysUpTime object (which defines when a specific occurrence happened).

infoString.name: infoString
infoString.description: When applicable, a brief description about the notification.

memoryUsed.name: memoryUsed
memoryUsed.description: The amount of disk space or memory consumed by the hard disk/RAM. This value can be absolute or a percentage of total (determined by 'memoryUsageType'). If the memoryUsageType is 'absolute' (1) then the value of this object is defined by the unit specified by the memoryUsageUnit.

memoryUsageType.name: memoryUsageType
memoryUsageType.description: The type of the value contained in 'memoryUsed' (which can be an 'absolute' value or a 'percentage' of the total value).

memoryUsageUnit.name: memoryUsageUnit
memoryUsageUnit.description: The unit of measurement for the value contained in 'memoryUsed'. If the value of 'memoryUsageType' is 'absolute', then this object will have one of the first three values. If the value of 'memoryUsageType' contains 'percentage', then this object will have the value of 'none'.

alarmSeverity.name: alarmSeverity
alarmSeverity.description: These provide an indication of how the capability of the iSD/Switch has been affected. These severity levels, which represent service affecting conditions, are ordered from most severe to least severe (ss defined in X.733 standard).

deviceMACAddress.name: deviceMACAddress
deviceMACAddress.description: The MAC address of the iSD/switch emitting the notification.

asfAcceleratorAddedTrap.name: asfAcceleratorAddedTrap
asfAcceleratorAddedTrap.description: Trap sent when an accelerator is added to the cluster.

asfAcceleratorRemovedTrap.name: asfAcceleratorRemovedTrap
asfAcceleratorRemovedTrap.description: Trap sent when an accelerator is removed from the cluster.

asfExtraAcceleratorDetected.name: asfExtraAcceleratorDetected
asfExtraAcceleratorDetected.description: Trap sent when an extra accelerator is detected in the cluster. This trap contains the MAC address of the extra accelerator.

asfAcceleratorConnEstablished.name: asfAcceleratorConnEstablished
asfAcceleratorConnEstablished.description: Trap sent when a connection has been established with the accelerator. This trap contains the MAC address of the accelerator.

asfConfigUpdateSuccess.name: asfConfigUpdateSuccess
asfConfigUpdateSuccess.description: Informative trap sent conveying that the configuration update request is successfully completed. This trap sends the IP address and MAC address of the device whose update succeeded.

asfConfigUpdateFail.name: asfConfigUpdateFail
asfConfigUpdateFail.description: Informative trap sent conveying that the configuration update request failed. This trap sends the IP address and MAC address of the device whose update failed.

asfFirewallStarted.name: asfFirewallStarted
asfFirewallStarted.description: Trap sent when the firewall has started running. This trap contains the IP address of relevant iSD.

asfIsdFirewallFail.name: asfIsdFirewallFail
asfIsdFirewallFail.description: Trap sent when the firewall on one of the iSDs in the cluster is stopped. This trap contains the IP address of the affected iSD.

asfWebServerFail.name: asfWebServerFail
asfWebServerFail.description: Trap sent when webserver is stopped. This trap contains the IP address of the affected iSD.

asfWebServerStart.name: asfWebServerStart
asfWebServerStart.description: Trap sent when webserver is started after failing. This trap contains the IP address of the affected iSD.

asfFileSystemWarning.name: asfFileSystemWarning
asfFileSystemWarning.description: Trap sent when file system usage crosses 75% level. For example, if level crosses 75% for 1 GB hard disk on iSD with IP address 123.45.67.89, then a trap is sent when usage of hard disk is reaches 750 MB. The following objects will be in the trap: 123.45.67.89, bytes (used), bytes (available).

asfFileSystemCritical.name: asfFileSystemCritical
asfFileSystemCritical.description: Trap sent when file system usage crosses 90% level. For example, if level crosses 90% for 1 GB hard disk on iSD with IP address 123.45.67.89, then a trap is sent when usage of hard disk reaches 900 MB. The following objects will be in the trap: 123.45.67.89, bytes (used), bytes (available).

asfMemoryWarning.name: asfMemoryWarning
asfMemoryWarning.description: Trap sent when memory usage crosses 75% level. The following objects will be in the trap: iSD IP address, 75% used, % memory available.

asfMemoryCritical.name: asfMemoryCritical
asfMemoryCritical.description: Trap sent when memory usage crosses 90% level. The following objects will be in the trap: iSD IP address, 90% used, % memory available.

asfIsdStateDown.name: asfIsdStateDown
asfIsdStateDown.description: Trap sent when the iSD's state is down. This trap contains the IP address of the affected iSD.

asfPortStats.name: asfPortStats
asfPortStats.description: This group contains the byteCount and packet count statistics per port.

asfPortNetStatsTime.name: asfPortNetStatsTime
asfPortNetStatsTime.description: The current time at the accelerator.

asfPortNetStatsTable.name: asfPortNetStatsTable
asfPortNetStatsTable.description: Each row in the table gives the information about an individual port.

asfPortNetStatsEntry.name: asfPortNetStatsEntry
asfPortNetStatsEntry.description: The isd information about the row selected.

asfPortCountIndex.name: asfPortCountIndex
asfPortCountIndex.description: The index of the portStatsTable which specifies the individual port.

asfPortInBytes.name: asfPortInBytes
asfPortInBytes.description: The number of bytes ingressing the port.

asfPortOutBytes.name: asfPortOutBytes
asfPortOutBytes.description: The number of bytes egressing the port.

asfPortInPackets.name: asfPortInPackets
asfPortInPackets.description: The number of packets ingressing the port. This is the sum of ingressing unicast, broadcast, multicast, discarded, unknown, and error packets.

asfPortOutPackets.name: asfPortOutPackets
asfPortOutPackets.description: The number of packets egressing the port. This is the sum of egressing unicast, broadcast, multicast, discarded, and unknown packets.

asfPortInUcastPackets.name: asfPortInUcastPackets
asfPortInUcastPackets.description: The number of unicast packets ingressing the port.

asfPortOutUcastPackets.name: asfPortOutUcastPackets
asfPortOutUcastPackets.description: The number of unicast packets egressing the port.

asfPortInBcastPackets.name: asfPortInBcastPackets
asfPortInBcastPackets.description: The number of broadcast packets ingressing the port.

asfPortOutBcastPackets.name: asfPortOutBcastPackets
asfPortOutBcastPackets.description: The number of broadcast packets egressing the port.

asfPortInMcastPackets.name: asfPortInMcastPackets
asfPortInMcastPackets.description: The number of multicast packets ingressing the port.

asfPortOutMcastPackets.name: asfPortOutMcastPackets
asfPortOutMcastPackets.description: The number of multicast packets egressing the port.

asfPortInDiscards.name: asfPortInDiscards
asfPortInDiscards.description: The number of ingressing packets discarded.

asfPortOutDiscards.name: asfPortOutDiscards
asfPortOutDiscards.description: The number of egressing packets discarded.

asfPortInErrors.name: asfPortInErrors
asfPortInErrors.description: The number of ingressing packets with errors.

asfPortOutErrors.name: asfPortOutErrors
asfPortOutErrors.description: The number of egressing packets with errors.

asfPortInUnknowns.name: asfPortInUnknowns
asfPortInUnknowns.description: The number of unknown ingressing packets.

asfIsdStats.name: asfIsdStats
asfIsdStats.description: This group contains the session count statistics per isd.

asfIsdSessStatsTime.name: asfIsdSessStatsTime
asfIsdSessStatsTime.description: The current time at the accelerator.

asfIsdSessStatsTable.name: asfIsdSessStatsTable
asfIsdSessStatsTable.description: Each row in the table gives the information about the session count on the isd which is per isd .

asfIsdSessStatsEntry.name: asfIsdSessStatsEntry
asfIsdSessStatsEntry.description: The isd information about the row selected.

asfIsdCountIndex.name: asfIsdCountIndex
asfIsdCountIndex.description: The index of the isdStatsTable which specifies the isd.

asfIsdIPAddress.name: asfIsdIPAddress
asfIsdIPAddress.description: The IP address of the isd.

asfNoOfSessions.name: asfNoOfSessions
asfNoOfSessions.description: The number of sessions on this isd.
